# Push after every commit

When the user asks to commit (or when a commit is created at their request):

1. Complete the commit following the normal git commit protocol.
2. Immediately push to the tracked remote branch (`git push -u origin HEAD` if upstream is missing, otherwise `git push`).
3. Do not wait to be asked to push — push is part of the commit workflow for this repo.
4. Report the remote result (branch + short SHA) after the push.
5. Still never force-push unless the user explicitly requests it.
